  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Reduction in Pain Score</measure>
    <time_frame>After 9 doses, expected average 1 month</time_frame>
    <description>The primary analysis is testing and estimating the effect of ketamine in comparison to placebo. Pain assessment will be analyzed using descriptive statistics. We will also determine average pain scores and average duration of analgesia. The effect of ketamine in comparison to placebo will be estimated with a mean and confidence interval. Proportional reductions in pain scores (post-treatment pain score ÷ pre-treatment pain score) will be calculated and similarly analyzed. The proportion of subjects experiencing a reduction in pain scores of &gt;33% will be calculated.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
